This memorandum, issued by President Donald Trump on December 11, 2017, focuses on reinvigorating America's human space exploration program. It specifically amends Presidential Policy Directive-4, which is the National Space Policy. The amendment emphasizes leading an innovative and sustainable program of exploration with commercial and international partners to enable human expansion across the solar system. It also states the intention to bring back new knowledge and opportunities to Earth. The amendment further highlights the United States' goal of returning humans to the Moon for long-term exploration and utilization, followed by human missions to Mars and other destinations. The memorandum includes general provisions that clarify the implementation of the directive, ensuring it complies with applicable laws and is subject to the availability of appropriations. It also states that the memorandum does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party. The memorandum is to be published in the Federal Register.